      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPRING NICK (1) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fourth wasn't far away finishing 1.5 lengths from the winner (16.71). Form here at the trip sound including five wins. Ready to return to form. SMOOTH PANTHER (2) finished well back at Capalaba last time when a 9 length eighth (20.62) but scored five back at Warragul (22.92). Has a good record here at this journey. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings five times from nine attempts. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. HARA'S TREVOR (3) comes off an average effort last start when seventh at Q Straight over 300m behind Shian Mikey (17.16) in a Grade 5. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Has ability and can atone. BORNEO KAWAII (5) was a surprise winner last time, don't underestimate.",
